🏷️ 🔥 NAMING CONVENTION (USE THIS EXACTLY)

Let’s assume:

Project = xyz
Environment = prod
Region = centralindia
Resource	Name
Resource Group	rg-xyz-prod-ci
VNet	vnet-xyz-prod-ci
App Service	app-xyz-prod-ci
App Plan	asp-xyz-prod-ci
SQL Server	sql-xyz-prod-ci
SQL DB	sqldb-xyz-prod
App Gateway	agw-xyz-prod-ci
Key Vault	kv-xyz-prod-ci
VM (Jumpbox)	vm-xyz-jump-prod
Bastion	bas-xyz-prod-ci
Private Endpoint	pe-sql-xyz-prod
🧱 🔥 PHASE 1: NETWORK SETUP
✅ Step 1: Create Resource Group

👉 Azure Portal

Search: Resource Groups
Click Create

Fill:

Name: rg-xyz-prod-ci
Region: Central India
✅ Step 2: Create VNet

👉 Search: Virtual Networks → Create

Fill:

Name: vnet-xyz-prod-ci
Address Space: 10.0.0.0/16
✅ Step 3: Create Subnets

Inside VNet → Subnets:

Subnet	Address
app-subnet	10.0.1.0/24
pe-subnet	10.0.2.0/24
vm-subnet	10.0.3.0/24
AzureBastionSubnet	10.0.4.0/27
🗄️ 🔥 PHASE 2: SQL DATABASE (PRIVATE)
✅ Step 4: Create SQL Server + DB

👉 Search: SQL Database → Create

Fill:

DB Name: sqldb-xyz-prod
Server: sql-xyz-prod-ci
Authentication: SQL + Azure AD
✅ Step 5: Disable Public Access
Go to SQL Server → Networking
Select:
Public Network Access = Disable
✅ Step 6: Create Private Endpoint

👉 SQL → Networking → Private Endpoint → Add

Fill:

Name: pe-sql-xyz-prod
VNet: vnet-xyz-prod-ci
Subnet: pe-subnet

👉 Enable:
✔ Private DNS Integration

🌐 🔥 PHASE 3: APP SERVICE
✅ Step 7: Create App Service Plan

👉 Search: App Service Plan

Name: asp-xyz-prod-ci
SKU: B1 / S1
✅ Step 8: Create App Service

👉 Search: Web App

Name: app-xyz-prod-ci
Plan: above plan
✅ Step 9: Enable Managed Identity

👉 App Service → Identity

Turn System Assigned = ON
✅ Step 10: VNet Integration

👉 App Service → Networking

VNet Integration → Add
Select app-subnet
✅ Step 11: Private Endpoint for App

👉 App Service → Networking → Private Endpoint → Add

Subnet: pe-subnet
🔐 🔥 PHASE 4: KEY VAULT + CERTIFICATE
✅ Step 12: Create Key Vault

👉 Search: Key Vault

Name: kv-xyz-prod-ci
✅ Step 13: Upload PFX Certificate

👉 Key Vault → Certificates → Import

Upload .pfx
🌍 🔥 PHASE 5: APPLICATION GATEWAY
✅ Step 14: Create Application Gateway

👉 Search: Application Gateway

Name: agw-xyz-prod-ci
Tier: WAF v2
✅ Step 15: Configure
🔹 Frontend
Public IP
🔹 Listener
HTTPS (443)
Select cert from Key Vault
🔹 Backend Pool
Add App Service
🔹 Routing Rule
Connect Listener → Backend
🌐 🔥 PHASE 6: DNS + DOMAIN
✅ Step 16: DNS Mapping

In your domain provider:

A Record:
www.xyz.com → App Gateway Public IP
🛠️ 🔥 PHASE 7: ADMIN ACCESS
✅ Step 17: Create Jump Box VM

👉 VM → Create

Name: vm-xyz-jump-prod
Subnet: vm-subnet
✅ Step 18: Create Bastion

👉 Bastion → Create

Subnet: AzureBastionSubnet
✅ Step 19: Connect
Laptop → Bastion → VM → SQL
🔐 🔥 PHASE 8: ON-PREM AD INTEGRATION
✅ Step 20: Sync AD to Azure

👉 Install:
Azure AD Connect on on-prem server

Steps:

Download Azure AD Connect
Install → Express Settings
Sync users to Azure
✅ Step 21: Set Azure AD Admin for SQL

👉 SQL Server → Azure AD Admin

Select synced user
✅ Step 22: Grant DB Access

Run in SSMS:

CREATE USER [user@domain.com] FROM EXTERNAL PROVIDER;
ALTER ROLE db_owner ADD MEMBER [user@domain.com];
🔄 🔥 PHASE 9: DATA MIGRATION
✅ Option 1: Azure Data Migration Service (BEST)
Steps:
Create Azure DMS
Source: SQL VM (IaaS)
Target: Azure SQL DB
Start Migration
✅ Option 2: Backup & Restore
Take backup from SQL VM
Upload to Azure Storage
Restore to Azure SQL
🔐 🔥 FINAL SECURITY CHECK

✔ WAF enabled
✔ SQL private
✔ App private
✔ Managed Identity
✔ Key Vault
✔ Bastion access

🎯 FINAL FLOW
User → DNS → App Gateway → App Service → Private Endpoint → SQL
Admin → Bastion → VM → SQL
